    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "using: Currently, libraries also contain lots of other things, most notably structs, but I would be fine with restricting `using` to only namespaces with only functions. I would not disallow functions with different first parameter type because it gives you some flexibility about how to group functions, but am also not too strong on this.\r\n\r\nI would not allow namespaces to be re-opened.\r\n\r\nAbout modifiers: it is probably not very useful to have a modifier that does not have access to state variables, but we can still allow it.\r\n\r\nI think we should move away from the word library, it has been used for too many different things.",
