    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If we allow `using A.* for B` where `A` is an imported module without adding explicit namespaces or named modules, one tiny problem that still needs to be solved is if we want to allow `using A for B` at file level - as a replacement for it being used inside a library.\r\n\r\nI think allowing `using A for B` at file level could also simplify the language. One issue with `using` we have is that it is not clear how it behaves with inheritance. I think it is more justifiable that `import \"abc\"` does not \"import\" the effects of \"using\" - and certainly `import \"abc\" as X` does not import it.",
